The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 September is 71,130 (8,198.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 September, there were 2,394 new confirmed cases (275.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 August, there were 2,088 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 15% (306 extra cases).
